climbs.name: Wild Thing
climbs.fa: Bolted by Chris Barnes, Vernon Phinney, & Mike Engle; FA Andrew Thaller; 2016

content.description: Start in the same corner as Buck Fever and move right to an undercling below a big roof. Reach out and gain a series of hueco features and follow them up the wildly overhanging arête until you can pull left onto the face. Continue on the face with moderate climbing to the anchors.

climbs.name: The Whuppin’
climbs.fa: Bolted by Chris Barnes, Vernon Phinney, & Mike Engle; 2018

content.description: Climb up grey stone and move over a small roof into a shallow corner. Continue up hard moves to a second roof and head right on tan rock to shallow tan obtuse corner.  Great climb with continuous movement.

climbs.name: Warpath
climbs.fa: Bolted by Chris Barnes, Vernon Phinney, & Mike Engle; 2018

content.description: Start on a sandy ledge a few feet off the ground. Work up a corner with body smears to gain a couple difficult holds. Continue up the corner until you can make easier moves to the left. Work up to a stance below a corner. Continue up the corner to a small, fun roof up and slightly left. Pull the roof and continue on easier terrain to the anchors.

climbs.name: Thor’s Hammer
climbs.fa: Bolted by Chris Barnes, Vernon Phinney, & Mike Engle; 2016

content.description:
Climb tough opening moves up grey rock to a stance below a small roof. Exit to the right (10-) or stay left and pull the roof (10). Both variations finish on the same anchor.

Named for Vernon Phinney's aggressive cleaning from big blocks at the rim of the cliff above the climb.  The aftermath makes good seats for putting on your shoes at the base of the climb.

climbs.name: Steep Thrills
climbs.fa: Bolted by Chris Barnes, Vernon Phinney, & Mike Engle; 2018

content.description: Scramble up to left diagonalling crack. Face climb from the left or make a couple jams to a stance. Continue straight up on pinches and crimps to the anchors.

climbs.name: Shogun
climbs.fa: Bolted and FA by Terran Engle; 2016

content.description: Pull a small roof off the ground to a steep shallow dihedral with thin crimps.  Crimp and stem to the right side of a large overhang.  Climb the corner above to a stance below the final face.

climbs.name: Sandstorm
climbs.fa: FA Andrew Thaller and Preston Perkins; 2016.

content.description: This is the middle of three routes on the shortface on the uphill side of Send Town. Move up and right over a bulge to a small roof. Pull over the roof into a shallow corner and crimp to the anchors.  Short, fun, and powerful.

climbs.name: Rocktoberfest
climbs.fa: Bolted by Chris Barnes, Vernon Phinney, & Mike Engle; FA by Andrew Thaller; 2016

content.description: Start on the right side of the large cave and fire pit. Climb up to a stance below an obvious overhanging smooth corner with a jam/lieback crack. Struggle to the lip and do a burly pull onto a small ledge. Continue up two short but challenging overhanging corners to the anchors on the rim.  Great route.

climbs.name: Road Warrior
climbs.fa: Bolted by Chris Barnes, Vernon Phinney, & Mike Engle; 2016

content.description: Start on a short vertical wall and pull onto a ledge. Continue on easy ground to a large roof and pull through with a tough barn door lie back to a stance over the roof. Continue on steep terrain to a small roof at the top. Pass it on the right and pull up to the anchors.

climbs.name: Ms. Snatchural
climbs.fa: Bolted by Chris Barnes, Vernon Phinney, & Mike Engle; 2016.  2nd pitch added by Barnes, Phinney, & Engle in 2018 and goes at 5.11

content.description:
,

Pitch 1 (5.9): start left of the large cave and work right into a large slot. Move up and right to a stance below a feature face. Fun face climbing leads to the anchors below some stacked blocks (about 40 feet below the rim).

Pitch 2 (5.11):  Climb up and left around an outside corner and pass a roof system to the anchors.

Can be done in one long pitch but adds a difficult roof (5.11+?) staying left of the P1 anchors.

climbs.name: Mad Max
climbs.fa: Bolted by Chris Barnes, Vernon Phinney, & Mike Engle; 2016

content.description: Climb vertical grey rock to a small ledge, continue up to the first of 3 roofs. A heel hook leads to a hard pull with a lot of body tension over the first roof. Pass the second roof on the left. Pass the 3rd roof on the right and work up a crux corner to a horn like feature and a hard pull to the anchors.

climbs.name: Jailbait
climbs.fa: FA Preston Perkins; 2016.

content.description: This is the rightmost route at Send Town.  Climb up streaked tan and grey rock to an obtuse corner.  Continue up the corner to the anchors.

climbs.name: Holier Than Thou
climbs.fa: Bolted by Chris Barnes, Vernon Phinney, & Mike Engle; 2016

content.description: Take the left side of a prow through featured ‘bubble rock’ to a suspect looking flake. Take care not to snap it off and pull through to gain easier terrain. Shares last bolt and anchors with Holey Moley and anchors with Holey Roller.

climbs.name: Holey Roller
climbs.fa: Bolted by Chris Barnes, Vernon Phinney, & Mike Engle; 2016

content.description: Climb up featured rock to an obvious thin finger crack. This is the left route of three routes that share the same anchor. Shares anchors with Holier Than Thou and Holey Moley.

climbs.name: Holey Moley
climbs.fa: Bolted by Chris Barnes, Vernon Phinney, & Mike Engle; 2016

content.description: Climb on the right side of a prow like formation with swiss cheese features. Pull left around a steep edge to a stance. Follow easy rock to the anchors.

climbs.name: The Gloves Go On
climbs.fa: Bolted by Chris Barnes, Vernon Phinney, & Mike Engle; 2018

content.description: Stick clip the first bolt and boulder up to the bulging hand crack, pull into the offwidth and exit right to ledge. Move left and climb a fun corner on excellent rock.

climbs.name: The Gloves Come Off
climbs.fa: Bolted by Chris Barnes, Vernon Phinney, & Mike Engle; 2016

content.description: Stand on a small boulder under a roof. Pull up on starting holds to gain a block. Use the block to gain the hand crack.  Burly initial thin hands lead to more solid hands. Pull onto a ledge and gain the top of a small pillar. Pull on to a classic prow and face climb for 3 more bolts to the anchors.  Super fun!

climbs.name: Futurama
climbs.fa: Bolted by Chris Barnes, Vernon Phinney, & Mike Engle; FA by Charlie Elverson; 2016.

content.description: Move up and left to an undercling flake below a small roof. Climb left on underclings and gain small holds just above the lip. Crank through roof to the anchors. Short, powerful.

climbs.name: Flop Sweat
climbs.fa: Bolted by Chris Barnes and FA by Andrew Thaller, 2016.

content.description: Climb up a steep corner and move over a bulge and right to a face below the anchors.

climbs.name: Entropy
climbs.fa: Bolted by Chris Barnes, Vernon Phinney, & Mike Engle; 2018

content.description: Shares the first two bolts with Chaos.  Chaos moves up and left while Entropy continues straight up the crack.  About 15 feet of tough sledding leads to finally a good jam.  Continue up the 5.10 crack to the anchors.   Great route.
content.location: Starts about 50 feet up and left from the big, gross party cave.

climbs.name: No Time
climbs.fa: Bolted by Chris Barnes, Vernon Phinney, & Mike Engle; FA by Andrei Zippy; 2016

content.description: Climb up to the bottom of a large prow and move right into a right facing corner. Stem, face climb and jam up to a blocky small roof. Pull through and climb to the anchors.  Fun, moderate warm up.

climbs.name: Egomaniacs
climbs.fa: Bolted by Chris Barnes, Vernon Phinney, & Mike Engle; 2018

content.description:
Scramble up to stance below an obvious nice looking corner.  Stem up and until it possible to pull into the right hand

crack.  Continue up into a very nice corner system. The route ends at the top of the corner and under a small roof.

climbs.name: Dust Devil
climbs.fa: Bolted by Chris Barnes, Vernon Phinney, & Mike Engle; 2016

content.description: Climb up tricky slab moves into a creamy colored right leaning double dihedral, stem up to the roof and pull through on mostly big holds.  Excellent climb on great rock.

climbs.name: Desert Solitaire
climbs.fa: Bolted by Chris Barnes, Vernon Phinney, & Mike Engle; 2016

content.description: Climb up featured rock to a major blocky roof. Continue up to another small roof and finish on thin tip jams.

climbs.name: Danger Zone
climbs.fa: Bolted by Chris Barnes, Vernon Phinney, & Mike Engle; 2018

content.description: The start is a little squeezed between Dust Devil and Slave Boy, jam a small roof just off the ground. Continue on a fully independent line up through 2 more roofs to the anchors.  3 cruxes.

climbs.name: Chaos (Open project)
climbs.fa: Bolted by Andrew Thaller

content.description: Climb up to the start of a white crack.  Traverse left on tiny crimps to a blunt outside corner.  Continue up on small crimps.  Thought to be 13.

climbs.name: Caleb’s Corner
climbs.fa: Bolted by Chris Barnes, Vernon Phinney, & Mike Engle; FA by Toddo Joyal; 2016

content.description: Climb up to the bottom of a large prow and move to the corner left of the prow on insecure liebacking. Once established, follow the corner system to the anchors.

climbs.name: Buck Fever
climbs.fa: Bolted by Chris Barnes, Vernon Phinney, & Mike Engle; 2016

content.description: Climb up featured grey rock with huecos and pull a small roof into a long right facing corner that gets steeper towards its top. Move over a small overlap and continue up to an awkward clip at the anchors.  First climb bolted at Send Town.  Great warm up climb.

climbs.name: Black Ops
climbs.fa: Bolted by Chris Barnes, Vernon Phinney, & Mike Engle; 2016.  FA by Tom Burton, 2020.

content.description: Climb up to a really hard pull through a bulge at mid height.

climbs.name: Black Lung
climbs.fa: Bolted by Chris Barnes, Vernon Phinney, & Mike Engle; 2018

content.description: Climb up sandy hueco’s and make a thin move and long reach to a ledge. Follow steep rock to a final committing overhang.  FA:  Mike Engle, Chris Barnes, SupeVitali Mar 19, 2017.

climbs.name: Beginning of the End (aka JR’s An Asshole)
climbs.fa: Bolted by Chris Barnes, Vernon Phinney, & Mike Engle; 2018

content.description:
Climb the corner system right of big graffiti “JR”.  Begin the lie back moves of

Barely Legal

then move left under a flake and small roof.  Pull the roof and follow a crack to the next larger roof.  Big moves up and left through the roof.

climbs.name: Beat Down
climbs.fa: Bolted by Chris Barnes, Vernon Phinney, & Mike Engle; FA by Terran Engle; 2016

content.description:
Climb up to the right side of the same roof as Slave Boy and make a hard and balancy pull over the roof and onto the black slabby face. Dance through a tricky section with some rat poop and pull through the roof to a thin finish on excellent tan and brown rock.

During an FA attempt, Terran unintentionally discovered that Mike and Chris had drilled the last bolt but forgot to put the bolt and hanger in it.  Unfortunately, he took a massive whip on the hard finish at the anchors.  After the missing bolt was installed, Terran went back and sent the route.  The crux is still pulling onto the slab above the roof 10 feet off the ground.

climbs.name: Barely Legal
climbs.fa: Bolted by Mike Engle, FA by Andrew Thaller; 2016

content.description: Start 15’ left of the big cave with the huge fire ring. Scramble up blocks to a right facing corner with a lieback crack, move right to an undercling flake to gain another crack, then pull a small bulge. Continue up a steep, ramped corner to a huge roof. Pull the roof at its weakest point and power through a blocky overhang on mostly big holds. Step left and finish on an easier face.
